ing objectives simultaneously in a mathematical model.\"", "\"PARETO EFFICIENCY\":\"Pareto efficiency is a state where it is impossible to make any one individual better off without making at least one individual worse off. It is used in multi-objective optimization.\"", "\"STOCHASTIC OPTIMIZATION\":\"Stochastic optimization involves optimization problems that include randomness. It is used when the objective function or constraints are uncertain.\"", "\"DETERMINISTIC OPTIMIZATION\":\"Deterministic optimization involves optimization problems with no randomness. The objective function and constraints are known with certainty.\"", "\"DYNAMIC PROGRAMMING\":\"Dynamic programming is a method for solving complex problems by breaking them down into simpler subproblems. It is applicable to optimization problems.\"", "\"NETWORK OPTIMIZATION\":\"Network optimization involves finding the optimal way to design and operate a network, such as a transportation or communication network.\"", "\"SUPPLY CHAIN OPTIMIZATION\":\"Supply chain optimization involves improving the efficiency and effectiveness of a supply chain by optimizing the flow of goods, information, and finances.\"", "\"PORTFOLIO OPTIMIZATION\":\"Portfolio optimization involves selecting the best portfolio of assets to maximize return and minimize risk.\"", "\"SCHEDULING OPTIMIZATION\":\"Scheduling optimization involves finding the best schedule for tasks or activities to achieve specific objectives, such as minimizing completion time or maximizing resource utilization.\"", "\"ROUTING OPTIMIZATION\":\"Routing optimization involves finding the best routes for vehicles or data packets to minimize travel time, distance, or cost.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}